HEADWORD: Protosilicate
<hw>Pro`to*sil"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Proto-</ets> + <ets>silicate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A silicate formed with the lowest proportion of silicic acid, or
having but one atom of silicon in the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

